Although I only spent two years completing my undergraduate degree, it provided me with opportunities to conduct research in both HCI and theoretical computer science, to collaborate with faculty and peers, and to begin defining my research interests. These experiences ultimately solidified my commitment to pursuing higher education and inspired me to conduct future research. I want to continue exploring algorithm design, contribute to theoretical CS research, and mentor the next generation of students. I hope through my PhD to explore algorithm design in various contexts and to explore deeper insights into mathematics and computer science as a whole.
